        "description: |\n",
        "  Tasiyagnunpa (or Western Meadowlark, or *sturnella neglecta*) migrates each year to nest on the Great Plains in the United States. Using crowd-sourced observations of these birds, we can see that migration happening throughout the year. In the process, you'll learn about an important type of geospatial data called **vector data**, which records where points, lines, and shapes on the Earth.\n",
